narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if you like Egyptians, interesting languages, or archaeology. Don't take it as an easy language credit- it's not. But seriously, when are you going to have the chance to learn hieroglyphics again?
Yes, I would definitely recommend this class. It meets only twice a week and is probaby the easiest language class at Yale.
I recommend this class. The course load is extremely manageable and very laid back. Everything is graded fairly. It's a great class.
If you want to learn hieroglyphic Middle Egyptian, you have no choice! Take this course. It is painless and will teach you what you need to know for a very basic grasp on the thing.
